---
description: Enforce Nuxt data-flow and service-layer API boundaries
alwaysApply: true
---

# Nuxt Data Flow Rules

- MUST enforce flow: `Page -> Composable -> Service -> API`.
- `pages/**` and `components/**` MUST NEVER call `$fetch`, `useFetch`, or `useAsyncData` directly against API endpoints.
- `composables/**` MUST orchestrate state and control flow (`data`, `loading`, `error`) and call services.
- `services/**` MUST contain API request logic only (transport, endpoint, response mapping).
- `server/api/**` MUST contain endpoint handlers and server-side logic only.

# Service and Composable Conventions

- Composable naming: `useXxx`.
- Service naming: `xxx.service.ts`.
- Services MUST NOT contain UI concerns (toasts, modal state, DOM behavior).
- Components/pages/layouts/middleware MUST NOT import API clients directly when a service exists.

# Allowed vs Forbidden

- Allowed: `useUsers()` calls `user.service.ts`, returns `{ data, loading, error, fetchUsers }`.
- Forbidden: direct API calls from `components/**`, `pages/**`, `layouts/**`, `middleware/**`.
- Forbidden: business workflow logic inside service files.

# Compliance Gate

- If a request asks for direct API call in page/component, refuse and move logic to composable + service.
- When creating a new service, enforce `xxx.service.ts` naming and composable consumption.
